527,IssuesEvent,2015-06-04 01:26:52+00:00,4576441,kbandla/dpkt,200847,kbandla,,,closed,IPv6 package sets wrong internet checksum,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/kbandla/dpkt/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/kbandla/dpkt/labels/imported', 'name': 'imported', 'color': 'FFFFFF'}]",[],1,"_From [avkulka...@gmail.com](https://code.google.com/u/101312390611904139269/) on August 15, 2008 13:39:24_

In __str__ in the class IP6, IP6 sets the checksum of the payload (TCP or
ICMP6) to 

self.data.sum = dpkt.in_cksum_done(s + self.nxt + len(p))

The correct statement is  
self.data.sum = dpkt.in_cksum_done(s + socket.htons(self.nxt + len(p)))

_Original issue: http://code.google.com/p/dpkt/issues/detail?id=10_",{},{}
