1204,IssuesEvent,2017-11-09 10:55:00+00:00,16331291,davisking/dlib,6259399,davisking,,,closed,Building with AVX/SSE on MSVC - possible bug in latest release,[],[],5,"Some time ago I've download and builded latest release (19.7). Today I was trying to improve the speed of my app (i'm using dlib for face detection + facial landmarks detection) and I found out that dlib was built without SSE4 and AVX. I tried to create new dlib solution using ths command line: 
`cmake -G ""Visual Studio 15 2017 Win64"" -DUSE_AVX_INSTRUCTIONS=ON -DUSE_SSE4_INSTRUCTIONS=ON ..\dlib-19.7`
At the end of log (console utput) I noticed this:
```
CMake Warning:
  Manually-specified variables were not used by the project:

    USE_AVX_INSTRUCTIONS
    USE_SSE4_INSTRUCTIONS
-- Build files have been written to: ......
```
and in the result soltuion the architecture wsn't set to AVX. In the current master(14acae3), everything is fine (same command line -> solution with architecture set to AVX == option ""/arch:AVX"" added). I think that the bug was already solved by this commit: https://github.com/davisking/dlib/commit/3b2d73db68d33b8d61f4b7906cfb52d90e353496#diff-543c916bb0793b3b0cd2917fad2d8314
Note the added file (set_compiler_specific_options.cmake) and line including this file added to dlib/CMakeLists.txt I think that in 19.7 - in my opinion those changes solved the problem. As far as i know, using SSE4/AVX is important for performance, so maybe it's good moment for the next release or some other solution which will make the ""downloaded by default"" (yes, i know about master/head, but a lot of people prefer latest release) version use SSE4&AVX ?
",{},{}
