2598,IssuesEvent,2017-07-04 21:01:07+00:00,11974348,evansd/whitenoise,19630,evansd,,,closed,Figure out how to make `runserver_nostatic` work with Channels,[],[],8,"At present, `runserver_nostatic` works by simply shadowing the `runserver` command from `contrib.staticfiles` and replacing it with the `runserver` command from Django core. However, this won't work with Channels, which needs its own [runserver command](https://github.com/andrewgodwin/channels/blob/master/channels/management/commands/runserver.py).

A possible approach might be to require that `runserver_nostatic` be at the top of the `INSTALLED_APPS` list and for it to discover the next highest priority `runserver` command (by inspecting the [app registry](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/1.9/ref/applications/#application-registry) and delegate to that, after setting the appropriate `--no-static` flag.

This is obviously more complex and fragile, but it would be nice to have a simple (for the user) solution which was agnostic as to whether Channels was being used.
",{},{}
