2962,IssuesEvent,2016-02-23 14:37:46+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,3080489,duclad,,,opened,"Numeric values not sorted, cache corrupted??",[],[],0,"Hi, 

I have a strange issue.
I have a table with large numbers inside a column(eg 1200100000000000004,1200100000000000012).
The table is generated by a template framework and the table sorter is initialized inside $(function () {}) which is declared in the body of the generated html.

For all the columns the sorting is working fine( I have text, date columns) only for this one it does not sort.
Looking with the debugger I noticed this when building the cache

(index)    ID                                      PASSWORD
row: 0	1200100000000000000	""f8bd0dsdswwe0f0712ec2a74c05c25920439b7a""	
row: 1	1200100000000000000	""a5wewwewf8cd4b9a2ac357833b9b5a30ddcc70""	
row: 2	1200100000000000000	""5c68f55e4efc7fad322811ewewwb2e9ewa9e5e5""

From what it seems the column containing the ids has the wrong value inside, the last 2 digits are always replaced by a 0.

This is what I see after the parsing is done:

(index)parser extractor string empty
(0) ID ""digit"" ""none"" ""none"" ""bottom""
(1) PASSWORD ""text"" ""none"" ""none"" ""bottom""

Could you give me a hint about what is wrong?

This is how I intitalize the tablesorter:

$(function () {
                $('#table').tablesorter({
                    widthFixed:false,
                    debug: true,
                    usNumberFormat:false,
                    stringTo:'none',
                    headerTemplate: '{content}', // Add icon for various themes
                    widgets: ['zebra', 'stickyHeaders'],

                    widgetOptions: {
                        // jQuery selector or object to attach sticky header to
                        stickyHeaders_attachTo: $('#output') // or $('.wrapper')
                    }
                });

            });

Thanks,
Claudiu",{},{}
