3918,IssuesEvent,2015-03-07 00:28:56+00:00,15516057,Miserlou/SoundScrape,1170618,ericwishom,,,opened,soundscrape stops downloading after making its way partially through likes,[],[],0,"Hi There @Miserlou,

First of all, this is a live saver, thank you so much!

Currently running into an issue where soundscrape starts iterating through and downloading all of my liked songs on soundcloud (username is ewish), but the process stops after 50.  I ran the following commands each time, and they each resulted in soundscrape stopping after 50 downloads.

$ soundscrape ewish -l
$ soundscrape ewish -l -f
$ soundscrape https://soundcloud.com/ewish/likes
$ soundscrape https://soundcloud.com/ewish/likes -f

The 51st song works fine when being downloaded as a track, i.e.
$ soundscrape https://soundcloud.com/ob-obrien/ob-obrien-schemin-up

Just for clarity, wondering if there a limit imposed?  Any way to get around this?

Thanks!",{},{}
