4081,IssuesEvent,2015-03-21 00:00:28+00:00,7433211,jmcnamara/XlsxWriter,1112058,kviktor,,,opened,Can't create more than 1024 columns,[],[],0,"I checked the documentation but couldn't find any pointers about the maximum number of columns. According to the Microsoft site xlsx can support 16,384 columns, however the excel file generated with XlsxWriter only has 1024 columns. 

```python
from xlsxwriter import Workbook

wb = Workbook(""test.xlsx"")
sheet1 = wb.add_worksheet(""test"")

for idx in xrange(2000):
    sheet1.write(1, idx, idx)

wb.close() 
```",{},{}
4083,IssuesEvent,2015-03-21 00:40:43+00:00,7433211,jmcnamara/XlsxWriter,94267,jmcnamara,,,closed,Can't create more than 1024 columns,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jmcnamara/XlsxWriter/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/jmcnamara/XlsxWriter/labels/todo', 'name': 'todo', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"I checked the documentation but couldn't find any pointers about the maximum number of columns. According to the Microsoft site xlsx can support 16,384 columns, however the excel file generated with XlsxWriter only has 1024 columns. 

```python
