4505,IssuesEvent,2017-03-21 12:43:53+00:00,65250725,glitchassassin/lackey,7684744,glitchassassin,,,closed,Debug log file cannot be updated,"[{'id': 421661451, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/glitchassassin/lackey/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}, {'id': 490202350, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/glitchassassin/lackey/labels/fix%20in%20testing', 'name': 'fix in testing', 'color': '0052cc', 'default': False}]",[],2,"Hi,
Just found that the debug log file was opened in 'r' mode so could not be updated.
It could be fixed by open in 'a' mode.
Also the '\r' is preferred after the log_entry so that the output text file is friendly in Windows.
Below is my quick fix to get it work for reference.

File: Settings.py
Method: def _write_log(self, log_type, log_time, message):


`


        elif self._log_file:
            # Otherwise write to file, if a file has been specified
            with open(self._log_file, 'a') as logfile:
                logfile.write(log_entry + '\r')
        else:
            # Otherwise, print to STDOUT
            print(log_entry)`",{},{}
