5188,IssuesEvent,2016-02-06 08:16:31+00:00,4386648,earwig/mwparserfromhell,637235,earwig,,,closed,template is interpreted as a text node if the order of its parameters is altered,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/earwig/mwparserfromhell/labels/aspect:%20parser', 'name': 'aspect: parser', 'color': '33EEAA'}]",[],4,"First of all, my compliments and gratitude for such a great tool.

When parsing the following code, the first node is not recognised as a template:

```mediawiki
{{l+|{{if|{{{tilde|}}}|-|--}}{{{3}}}|tr={{{tr2|}}}}}
```

```python3
>>> mwparserfromhell.__version__
'0.4.3'
>>> tree = mwparserfromhell.parse(""{{l+|{{if|{{{tilde|}}}|-|--}}{{{3}}}|tr={{{tr2|}}}}}"")
>>> [(type(x), x) for x in tree.nodes]
[(mwparserfromhell.nodes.text.Text, '{{l+|'),
 (mwparserfromhell.nodes.template.Template, '{{if|{{{tilde|}}}|-|--}}'),
 (mwparserfromhell.nodes.argument.Argument, '{{{3}}}'),
 (mwparserfromhell.nodes.text.Text, '|tr='),
 (mwparserfromhell.nodes.argument.Argument, '{{{tr2|}}}'),
 (mwparserfromhell.nodes.text.Text, '}}')]
```

However, after swapping the position of parameters, the outcome is as expected:

```mediawiki
{{l+|tr={{{tr2|}}}|{{if|{{{tilde|}}}|-|--}}{{{3}}}}}
```

```python3
>>> tree = mwparserfromhell.parse(""{{l+|tr={{{tr2|}}}|{{if|{{{tilde|}}}|-|--}}{{{3}}}}}"")
>>> [(type(x), x) for x in tree.nodes]
[(mwparserfromhell.nodes.template.Template,
  '{{l+|tr={{{tr2|}}}|{{if|{{{tilde|}}}|-|--}}{{{3}}}}}')]
```

I have tested the issue in python versions 2.7.9 and 3.4.3",{},{}
