5795,IssuesEvent,2018-08-22 00:34:11+00:00,50591651,danielperna84/pyhomematic,7396998,danielperna84,,,closed,WEEK_PROGRAM_POINTER support for HM-TC-IT-WM-W-EU,[],[],12,"The wall-mounted Homematic thermostats support up to three different week programs („Wochenprogramme“). They are useful for people working in shifts to define different
heating profiles for different weeks/shifts.

The week programs can be changed through the CCU and through the XML-RPC API. It would be nice if pyhomematic could expose the week programs as attributes of the thermostat devices, so they could be set through Home Assistant.

For the HM-TC-IT-WM-W-EU this is the XMLRPC-API call which is required for changing the profiles:

```python
conn.putParamset(""DEVICE_SERIAL_NUMBER"", ""MASTER"", {'WEEK_PROGRAM_POINTER': 0})
conn.putParamset(""DEVICE_SERIAL_NUMBER"", ""MASTER"", {'WEEK_PROGRAM_POINTER': 1})
conn.putParamset(""DEVICE_SERIAL_NUMBER"", ""MASTER"", {'WEEK_PROGRAM_POINTER': 2})
```

The current week program can also be retrieved:
```python
result = conn.getParamset(""DEVICE_SERIAL_NUMBER"", ""MASTER"")
result[""WEEK_PROGRAM_POINTER""] # will be 0, 1 or 2
