6056,IssuesEvent,2016-08-07 17:48:28+00:00,27728976,eisensheng/pytest-catchlog,72146,eisensheng,,,opened,Intriduce flake8 to ensure code styling consistency,[],[],0,"I would like to start a discussion on introducing Flake8 to check and ensure code styling consistency. 

The styling check should also be introduced into the ``tox.ini`` file to guarantee that styling mistakes are detected during test runs with travis. The goal is to ensure that code will be written in a consistent manner and confusion on styling for code contributions will be reduced.

Subjects I would like to discuss here are:

* Whenever it actually makes sense to enable flake8 now.
* Having travis to mark a build as failed whenever flake8 complained about something.
* Which plugins to use. (``flake8-docstrings``, ``flake8-import-order``, ``flake8-print``, … )
* Which warnings to enable and to disable.",{},{}
