6171,IssuesEvent,2016-01-18 04:10:03+00:00,22954701,noirbizarre/flask-restplus,3237256,awiddersheim,,,opened,Easier custom exception handling,[],[],0,"Currently, it can be difficult to document custom exceptions. I find myself doing something similar to the following:

```
class CustomException(Exception):
        '''
        Exception to raise when something bad happens.
        '''

        code = 500
        description = 'Something bad happened.'

class Foo(Resource):
        @api.response(CustomException.code, CustomException.description)
        def get(self):
                '''
                Gets Foo.
                '''

                ...
```

I really like the [raises](https://flask-restplus.readthedocs.org/en/stable/syntaxic_sugar.html#handle-errors-with-api-errorhandler-decorator) stuff that was added and would love to use that but in order to do so I need to write something like the following:

```
class CustomException(Exception):
        '''
        Exception to raise when something bad happens.
        '''

        code = 500
        description = 'Something bad happened.'

@api.errorhandler(CustomException)
@api.marshal_with(error_fields, code=400)
@api.header('My-Header',  'Some description')
def handle_fake_exception_with_header(error):
    '''This is a custom error'''
    return {'message': error.message}, 400, {'My-Header': 'Value'}

class Foo(Resource):
        def get(self):
                '''
                Gets Foo.

                :raises CustomException: Something bad happened.
                '''

                ...
```

Ideally, it would be great if things could be cut down to something like:

```
@api.exception
@api.marshal_with(error_fields, code=400)
@api.header('My-Header',  'Some description')
class CustomException(Exception):
        """"""
        Exception to raise when something bad happens.
        """"""

        code = 500
        description = 'Something bad happened.'

class Foo(Resource):
        def get(self):
                '''
                Gets Foo.

                :raises CustomException: Something bad happened.
                '''

                ...
```

This would add `CustomException()` as a response in the swagger spec that can get referenced the same way the error handlers do with `raises`.

How this would all work under the covers I'm not sure about yet but figured I'd post to get some feedback.",{},{}
