6485,IssuesEvent,2015-01-09 16:09:44+00:00,5525736,ColinDuquesnoy/QDarkStyleSheet,1681217,ColinDuquesnoy,,,closed,Styling a Line from Designer,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ColinDuquesnoy/QDarkStyleSheet/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ColinDuquesnoy/QDarkStyleSheet/labels/unstyled+widget', 'name': 'unstyled widget', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],2,"QDarkStyleSheet is a really nice stylesheet. I ran into a unstyled ""widget"", the ""Horizontal Line"" and ""Vertical Line"" in Qt Designer. [It is a QFrame with height 3, sunken shadow and line width equal to 1. You can see it if examine header generated by uic tool.](http://stackoverflow.com/a/13930601)

    QFrame[isLine=""true""] {
        background-color: #3A3939;
    }

The only way I can think to style it is to add a bool QProperty and use a dynamic property selector in the stylesheet. This is not the best solution because you have to remember to add the property every time.

    QFrame[height=""3""], QFrame[width=""3""] {
        background-color: #3A3939;
    }

Now that I'm typing this issue up, I thought of a second way to handle it, by checking if the width or height is 3 on qframes.

I don't know if either of these should be included in QDarkStyleSheet, but its worth mentioning in case someone has a better idea.",{},{}
6528,IssuesEvent,2017-05-11 18:04:50+00:00,82026170,emlynoregan/appenginetaskutils,13439795,tbrent,,,reopened,Wrong number of values to unpack in task.py,[],[],4,"I've run into a bug with `_run()` in `task.py`. The bug occurs sometimes and not others. I believe it might have something to do with how the function is pickled. The bug seems to occur only when larger functions are pickled, but not with smaller ones. 

The failure occurs on line 43 of `task.py`:
func, args, kwargs, passthroughargs = pickle.loads(data)

The exception is: `PermanentTaskFailure: need more than 3 values to unpack`. I believe it is occurring because sometimes `pickle.loads()` returns 3 values, and sometimes 4. I have been able to workaround this bug by making all my tasks accept optional headers, and using the following lines of code in `task.py`:

    try:
        func, args, kwargs, passthroughargs = pickle.loads(data)
    except Exception, e:
        try:
            func, args, kwargs = pickle.loads(data)
        except Exception, e:
            raise PermanentTaskFailure(e)
    kwargs[""headers""] = headers
    func(*args, **kwargs)

I've also noticed that if I don't set `""headers""` then `_run_from_datastore()` fails because it was expecting 2 arguments but only gets 1. 

Hope some of this is making sense. ",{},{}
