# Question

Having a rnn to predict a point in time, based in indirect inputs. This is not the 'normal' time series prediction in which the future is predicted on the last values, but on a bunch of other features. When training, the first S (let's say 50) outputs will not be accurate at all. This means, during training, I will provide at least 51 inputs (and hence, there will be 51 outputs as well - 1 output per input). Let's call this number T. I'd only like to use only the last outputs (T-50) for the parameter/weights estimation during training, omitting the first S. How can I do/achieve that in mxnet?",{},{}
