7624,IssuesEvent,2017-07-12 13:12:57+00:00,60273704,mozilla/DeepSpeech,5991088,tilmankamp,131524,mozilla,opened,Hosting language model binary outside of source tree,"[{'id': 386594040, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/DeepSpeech/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 636954491, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/mozilla/DeepSpeech/labels/Priority:%20P3', 'name': 'Priority: P3', 'color': 'b60205', 'default': False}]",[],0,"There are several problems with the way we host the language model binaries as part of the source tree:
 - Fresh cloning takes a very long time
 - First time users are usually not aware of the LFS requirement
 - Changing the language model over time will further blow up repository size

So - like the corpora - the language model binaries should be hosted outside the source tree:
 - Hosted on some service like S3
 - Download URLs should feature a version
 - Current binary version number being part of current source code
 - There is a /bin script to download the required version 
 - Removing LFS requirement
 - Potentially rewriting master history to get rid of old binaries (warning to all users(community in advance)
",{},{}
