8295,IssuesEvent,2015-04-20 20:44:23+00:00,1062237,libgit2/pygit2,46573,rutsky,394745,libgit2,opened,"Adding git repository in tests breaks git submodules ""--recursive"" behavior",[],[],0,"[Recently](https://github.com/libgit2/pygit2/commit/1361b2cce90f3c29b7b9d0f0f5c98f6a6eee8e75) `test/data/testrepo` directory was added with actual git repository contents.
This breaks git submodule's `--recursive` functionality:

```
$ git clone git@github.com:libgit2/pygit2.git
...
$ cd pygit2
$ git checkout 1361b2cce90f3c29b7b9d0f0f5c98f6a6eee8e75
...
$ git submodule update --init --recursive
No submodule mapping found in .gitmodules for path 'test/data/testrepo'
$ echo $?
1
$
```

Which breaks tools that rely on recursive submodules checkout, e.g. see this pip bug: ",{},{}
