8397,IssuesEvent,2016-10-19 11:43:16+00:00,1071027,paver/paver,59874,rcoup,477096,paver,opened,Make it simple to call help task by default,[],[],0,"Not sure if this is a doc issue or a code issue or both...

Goal: Make `paver` print out the same as `paver help`

After digging in the code, looks like `default` task is what we want. With `default = tasks.help` though, you get:
```
*** Problem with pavement:
/Users/rcoup/code/tulip/pavement.py
Task paver.tasks.help requires an argument (args) that is not present in the environment
```

Eventually I ended up with the following:
```
@task
@no_help
def default():
    environment.args = []
    tasks.help()
```

Seems like the former should Just Work™?",{},{}
