8535,IssuesEvent,2017-11-20 23:57:28+00:00,28201627,dropbox/nsot,138052,jathanism,559357,dropbox,opened,"Bug in circuit create serializer: Doesn't include the ""site"" field.","[{'id': 158828884, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dropbox/nsot/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"This isn't caught because we have few use-cases that include top-level objects that aren't using site-specific API endpoints. We are not testing for this either.

e.g. `POST /api/circuits/` is hardly tested if at all, while `POST /api/sites/1/circuits/` is the bulk of our testing. I'm pretty certain that a test in the former case would fail with an error about missing `site` (`site_id`) since this value passed in implicitly in the latter example (more common).

So this isn't an active bug, but it's one I noted while working on the `Protocol` feature.",{},{}
