8586,IssuesEvent,2017-01-11 13:53:28+00:00,2625205,robotframework/Selenium2Library,2665023,aaltat,574284,robotframework,closed,Change the Travis to run differently the acceptance test,"[{'id': 250692017, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotframework/Selenium2Library/labels/HIGH%20PRIORITY', 'name': 'HIGH PRIORITY', 'color': 'e11d21', 'default': False}, {'id': 253450496, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotframework/Selenium2Library/labels/Infrastructure', 'name': 'Infrastructure', 'color': 'C0C0C0', 'default': False}]",[],2,"Because there was some unexpected problems with Travis and the accessing the encrypted information (the Sauce Labs credentials) [1] we need to change how we run acceptance tests from the original plan.

 * For each PR, run with Firefox (provided by Travis), selenium 2/3 and Python 2/3. 
 * Create nightly/weekly build to run from master and run by using Sauce Labs by using different browsers.

[1] https://docs.travis-ci.com/user/environment-variables/#Defining-encrypted-variables-in-.travis.yml ",{},{}
8603,IssuesEvent,2017-08-16 15:15:54+00:00,2625205,robotframework/Selenium2Library,2665023,aaltat,574284,robotframework,closed,`Press Key` doesn't send hash character (#) to an input filed,[],[],1,"Hey y'all.

I think I may have found a bug on **Press Key** builtin method, reasonably confident :-), details as follows.
http://robotframework.org/Selenium2Library/Selenium2Library.html#Press%20Key

I've been sending keys like below for a input field
**01234\#56789+*** and
**01234#56789+*** and
**0123456789+*#** and
**\\\\35**
**\\35**
**0123456789+*\\35** where **\\35** is decimal value, please see ASCII table.

None of the above inputs for `Press Key` sends the character '#', 
**Input text** builtin method also removes the '#' character.
http://rtomac.github.io/robotframework-selenium2library/doc/Selenium2Library.html#Input%20Text
yes **press key** and **Input text** removes hash every single occasion.

**Some Additional questions only if someone could assist.**

I'm sending the character '#' through **execute javascript** like below as a workaround.
`execute javascript  document.getElementsByName('dialNo')[1].value=""0123456789+*#""`
I however couldn't provide the control back the webdriver once accomplishing it through java-script.
test keeps failing after completing the above javascript line.

could someone advise a better alternative please.

If I've gotten anything wrong or if you need more info, please let me know

Thanks
Niro",{},{}
8612,IssuesEvent,2016-12-25 22:25:31+00:00,33992192,wildfish/django-star-ratings,10036256,delneg,584286,wildfish,opened,IP address from request.META.get('REMOTE_ADDR') issue,[],[],0,"I came accross this error:
    **DataError at /ratings/18/3/ invalid input syntax for type inet: ""b''""**

After googling and i found the problem:
ip = self.request.META.get('REMOTE_ADDR') - this line in views.py gets the ip **only** from **REMOTE_ADDR**, however it should get it also from **HTTP_X_REAL_IP**, as described in [http://stackoverflow.com/questions/34238623/invalid-input-syntax-for-type-inet-db-error-in-django-app-with-postgres-and-gu](Stackoverflow)
Please look into this.
I will provide full logs/configs if needed, the setup is Django 1.10.3, Python 3.5.2, nginx 1.10.0, Postgresql 9.5",{},{}
