8701,IssuesEvent,2015-01-19 16:41:21+00:00,15728083,robotpy/pyfrc,567900,virtuald,640276,robotpy,opened,known hosts SSH problem,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotpy/pyfrc/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/robotpy/pyfrc/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"If you have multiple roborios and they have the same mDNS hostname, SSH will complain and won't allow the connection to succeed. The typical way one fixes this is sending the known hosts file to /dev/null.

