9123,IssuesEvent,2017-10-16 12:38:28+00:00,1953389,stripe/stripe-python,23086931,ob-stripe,856813,stripe,closed,Trailing newline in stripe.api_key makes POST data disappear,[],[],3,"So I've spent a bit of time scratching my head over a strange bug in which none of my customer emails were being saved.  Looking in the request log dashboard, the POST data was blank.

Eventually I figured it out.

If I use `stripe.api_key =` to set the key with a newline at the end of the string, it seems to cause the POST data to get lost somewhere along the pipeline (see [line 11 of this gist](https://gist.github.com/Yuffster/d87e422c3c6d5b90b1b97339f66b57a1/eccd3f38a66b711e1947f01ea2a3767e4a8bcea1#file-customer-py-L11)).

However, if I run`.strip()` on my API key string, it works as expected (again, [line 11](https://gist.github.com/Yuffster/d87e422c3c6d5b90b1b97339f66b57a1/7526f4ab90c6dabfbb47c44baea67d34d1536d60#file-customer-py-L11); notice the output includes the email and description).
",{},{}
