9583,IssuesEvent,2016-07-12 19:58:09+00:00,44370739,inveniosoftware/invenio-records-rest,5708796,nharraud,1157480,inveniosoftware,opened,views: enable pass_record decorator use resource subclasses,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio-records-rest/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]","[{'login': 'nharraud', 'id': 5708796, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5708796?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/nharraud', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/nharraud/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"**Use case:**
B2Share needs to customize some of the REST API views. In order to reuse provided resource classes, it would be great if it was possible to subclass them.

**Problem:**
Current [`pass_record` decorator](https://github.com/inveniosoftware/invenio-records-rest/blob/97ac2efcf8b63ab952c0ed9fe999e22b77211ef2/invenio_records_rest/views.py#L279) does not forward some of its arguments, i.e `pid_value`, to the wrapped function. Thus it is not possible to reuse it for subclasses.

**Optimization:**
In order to not try to retrieve the record and pid twice it would be necessary to check in the `pass_record` decorator's parameters if `pid` and `record` are already given (by a subclass calling its super class method).


**Impact on other modules:**
Other modules using `invenio-records-rest` will have to support additional arguments. This impacts at least `invenio-deposit`.",{},{}
