9679,IssuesEvent,2018-08-02 14:26:00+00:00,62325478,Linaro/squad,30027,terceiro,1180626,Linaro,closed,Be able to specify baseline when using email api,"[{'id': 401037610, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0MDEwMzc2MTA=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Linaro/squad/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 867401427, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw4Njc0MDE0Mjc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Linaro/squad/labels/high%20priority', 'name': 'high priority', 'color': 'db6dd7', 'default': False}]",[],5,"When calling the API like so:

https://qa-reports.linaro.org/api/builds/8275/email/

Note the line ""compared to build v4.14.56-93-gec86d5e19e14"".

Squad chooses the baseline (build v4.14.56-93-gec86d5e19e14 in this case) by naively using the previous build. However, my API client is able to determine a better baseline because it has knowledge of the project.

If the email endpoint allowed a 'baseline' build to be specified, perhaps like so: ""https://qa-reports.linaro.org/api/builds/8275/email?baseline=8156"", then the fixes and regressions that an email report produces would be much more useful.",{},{}
