10139,IssuesEvent,2018-07-09 08:09:05+00:00,71768806,hashedin/jinjasql,16999995,devashishsharma2302,1456904,hashedin,closed,Support passing JSON as dictionaries,[],[],1,"I'm trying to insert some JSON data into my database through JinjaSQL and Psycopg2. Though I'm getting stopped by JinjaSQL as it has the following check: https://github.com/hashedin/jinjasql/blob/93c9bbceedd45c2439a9b3698e9bddfc5df61958/jinjasql/core.py#L104

If we bypass this check and register an adaptor for dictionaries Psycopg2 will gladly eat the dictionary.

```
from psycopg2.extras import Json
register_adapter(dict, Json)

createAreaTemplate=""""""
  insert into  area_revisions (                                                                 
    area, modified_by, geo_json )                                                               
  values (                                                                                      
    {{ uuid }}, {{ modifiedBy }}, {{ geoJson }} )
""""""

area = {
    ""uuid"":            uuid4(),
    ""modifiedBy"":      author['uuid'],
    ""project"":         parentProject['uuid'],
    ""geoJson"":         """"
}

query, params = prepareQuery(createAreaTemplate, area)
a = list(params)
a[2] = {}
cursor.execute(query, parameters)
```

Would it be possible to remove the is_dictionary check?",{},{}
