10741,IssuesEvent,2018-05-11 20:02:14+00:00,73504243,Netflix-Skunkworks/cloudaux,1441598,reilings,1728142,Netflix-Skunkworks,opened,aws/iam.py: get_role_managed_policy_documents fails to pass connection details to internal calls,"[{'id': 577400907, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Netflix-Skunkworks/cloudaux/labels/AWS', 'name': 'AWS', 'color': 'F8B81F', 'default': False}, {'id': 479855010, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Netflix-Skunkworks/cloudaux/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'reilings', 'id': 1441598, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/1441598?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/reilings', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/reilings/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"`get_role_managed_policy_documents` passes its own `kwargs` directly to its internal calls to `get_role_managed_policies` and `get_managed_policy_document`, but the relevant connection parameters (`account_number`, `assume_role`, etc) are stripped by the `sts_conn` decorator beforehand. The result is that those internal calls receive no explicit connection parameters and fall back to boto3's credential-finding routine -- this may fail completely or pick up credentials that were not intended for this use.",{},{}
