11750,IssuesEvent,2016-06-03 20:47:53+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1883523,kwlzn,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Python constants in BUILD files not defined in new engine,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/engine', 'name': 'engine', 'color': 'fbca04'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/in-progress', 'name': 'in-progress', 'color': '009800'}]",[],5,"The [parser in use in the new engine](https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/master/src/python/pants/engine/legacy/parser.py) currently does not support variables defined in BUILD files.

A snippet like the following will cause an error indicating that the constant is an unknown symbol:
```
VERSION='1.0.0'

jar_library(name='foo', jars=[jar('org.bar', 'foo', VERSION)])
```",{},{}
