11794,IssuesEvent,2018-06-29 17:12:32+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1131704,illicitonion,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Expose materialize_directory as an intrinsic function on scheduler,[],"[{'login': 'dotordogh', 'id': 28027359, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjI4MDI3MzU5', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/28027359?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/dotordogh', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/dotordogh/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"`fs::Store` already has a function to materialize a directory to disk: https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/blob/2512e9b4c7aed6c1f681b544e8cc94c66553fb9c/src/rust/engine/fs/src/store.rs#L410-L414

We should expose this as an intrinsic function on the scheduler, so that python code can call `scheduler.materialize_directories((DirectoryToMaterialize('/path/to/materialize', directory_digest),))` with a tuple of pairs of paths (`str`) and directory digests (`DirectoryDigest`), and which returns when these directories exist.

This will look pretty similar to https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/pull/5801 which introduced a new intrinsic function, except this PR shouldn't need to change the `Scheduler` type.",{},{}
