11867,IssuesEvent,2016-12-31 07:05:06+00:00,15381974,groveco/django-sql-explorer,227869,anirvan-majumdar,3093407,groveco,opened,Avoid execution of parameterised queries when opening,[],[],0,"I have created and saved a bunch of queries and most of them rely on parameterisation. However, SQL Explorer attempts to execute the query everytime I click and open the query from the query listing page. If I've provided a default parameter value, then the explorer attempts to execute the query with the default, and if I haven't provided a default, it attempts to execute the query with the value set to `''`. In either case, the experience gets very sluggish, since the query execution with the default or '' value can take a _long_, _long_ time to execute.

It would be ideal if parameterised queries are _not_ executed when clicked to open.  

On a similar note, I also felt that there should be a simple ""Save"" option for queries. I can also see that #227 did indeed address this issue - but I'm not sure whether this has been released as part of version `1.0` which is currently available. Can you let me know when the next release is scheduled?

Thanks!",{},{}
