11996,IssuesEvent,2017-06-15 16:16:12+00:00,30618733,prometheus/client_python,7115638,brian-brazil,3380462,prometheus,closed,Implementing quantiles for Summary: exact or approximate?,[],[],4,"@brian-brazil welcomed PRs implementing quantiles for summaries in #92. I have a simplistic implementation that calculates quantiles exactly, but this requires keeping around all observations within the sliding window. I noticed that all other clients use Cormode and Muthukrishnan's [approximate algorithm](http://www.cs.rutgers.edu/~muthu/bquant.pdf). There is a Python package on [pyPI](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/quantile-python) that implements this algorithm. Would you prefer that it be used instead? I haven't used it myself, and it's marked in alpha status, but then again, so is the one used by the Ruby client.",{},{}
