12221,IssuesEvent,2018-02-06 20:21:35+00:00,66887069,learningequality/ricecooker,7447496,jayoshih,3926525,learningequality,closed,File list passed into a ContentNode must consist of more than just paths,[],"[{'login': 'aronasorman', 'id': 191955, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/191955?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/aronasorman', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/aronasorman/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'jayoshih', 'id': 7447496, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/7447496?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jayoshih', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jayoshih/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"So far, we've gotten away with passing in a list of simple string paths as `files` when instantiating `ContentNode` subclasses. E.g. `Document(files=[""http://mysite.com/somedoc.pdf""])`. It uses the class' `default_preset` to determine the preset for the file(s) in the list.

This won't be enough for many contexts. For example, once we start adding in subtitles, we'll need to indicate, for each of the subtitle files, what language it's for. We may also want to pass in options regarding caching, preprocessing, etc for each file.

I would propose having a `File` class, which takes a `path` (URL or file path), as well as an optional `preset` (or let it autodetect that, if desired). If appropriate to the preset, settings like `language` could also be passed in.

There could then also be subclasses of `File` that provide additional options, e.g. `VideoFile` that encapsulates the logic for doing resizing and other preprocessing.
",{},{}
