12626,IssuesEvent,2017-07-13 06:41:40+00:00,47576910,googlei18n/fontmake,142891,behdad,5503833,googlei18n,closed,Pipeline creates Myanmar fonts without GPOS entries for KSW and MON ,[],"[{'login': 'anthrotype', 'id': 6939968, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/6939968?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/anthrotype', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/anthrotype/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"copied from a report I received:
""This was found while checking the validity of the GSUB and GPOS in fonts created by pipeline. The designer states: ‘Myanmar is used in two other languages, Mon and Sgaw Karen, which are accounted for in our GPOS and GSUB. Pipeline seems to drop the two scripts from the GPOS.
GPOS in Pipeline Instances DO NOT carry over to Script Locales.

The code below was dumped from the Pipeline’s Noto Sans Myanmar Regular’s GPOS. The Regular instance is supposed to be equivalent in weight and width to the Noto Sans Myanmar Regular Master made by Monotype.
 
script table begin
mym2    default         0, 1, 2
script table end
 
However, the script table above is missing two locales present in our Regular Master:
 
script table begin
mym2    default         0, 1, 2
mym2   KSW           0, 1, 2
mym2   MON           0, 1, 2
script table end
 
As a result, when in a different locale, there is NO GPOS positioning taking place in the pipeline generated fonts.""


For reference:

- the source in question is in https://github.com/googlei18n/noto-source/tree/master/src/NotoSansMyanmar
- a sample font generated by the pipeline on 2017.March.1 is in https://github.com/googlei18n/noto-fonts/blob/master/alpha/from-pipeline/unhinted/otf/sans/NotoSans-Regular.otf",{},{}
