12744,IssuesEvent,2017-05-04 08:53:55+00:00,2113510,crossbario/autobahn-python,248980,OOPMan,5656948,crossbario,opened,register/subscribe decorators support different URI syntax from what session.register and session.subscribe support,[],[],0,"I'm not sure how this happened but it seems like the pattern-based URI syntax supported by the `register`/`subscribe` decorators and the underlying `Pattern` object that supports them is not actually supported by the `register`/`subscribe` methods on the `ApplicationSession` class.

Example:

```python
@wamp.register('a.b.c.<something>.e.f', options=RegisterOptions(match='wildcard', details_arg='details'))
def my_endpoint(details):
    pass
```

You would expect to be able to call that using:

```python
session.call('a.b.c.blahblahblah.e.f')
```
but doing so will yield a No Callee error.

However:

```python
session.call('a.b.c.<something>.e.f')
```
works when it probably shouldn't.

Additionally:

```python
@wamp.register('a.b.c..e.f', options=RegisterOptions(match='wildcard', details_arg='details'))
```
raises an exception

It seems like the support for this is only half-implemented at the moment or did some commits get lost in the woodwork?",{},{}
