12964,IssuesEvent,2016-01-21 19:58:49+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,1360539,bacongobbler,6117407,deis,closed,Unable to create a resources group on azure,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/contrib%20and%20provisioning', 'name': 'contrib and provisioning', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/deis/deis/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],5,"Hello,

I am trying to create my first azure 3-nodes deis cluster using an official tutorial (http://docs.deis.io/en/latest/installing_deis/azure/). However, i'm not able to do that using steps provided - there is one step that makes trouble: sshKeyData. I've searched for some other tutorials and found that all of them states the same so it must be something on my side. I just can't understand what i'm doing wrong so maybe someone here will help me.

Anyway - all the tutorials states that i need to, more or less, make the follwing (i've skipped the rest for simplicity's sake)

- generate a new ssh key `~/.ssh/deis(.pub)`
- add a content of `~/.ssh/deis` to `parameters.json` to `sshKeyData` value.
- run `azure group create (...)`
- add deis key `ssh-add -K ~/.ssh/deis`

However, for some reason, azure wont let me put contents of `~/.ssh/deis` as sshKeyData (i've removed the beginning and end lines and all the new-lines from it). When i try to run `azure group create` with `deis` key in `parameters.json`, i can see in the management portal that provisioning has failed because:

```
{""error"":{""code"":""InvalidParameter"",""target"":""linuxConfiguration.ssh.publicKeys.keyData"",""message"":""The value of parameter linuxConfiguration.ssh.publicKeys.keyData is invalid.""}}
```

I'm able to finalize a provisioning by providing `deis.pub` instead of `deis` contents but it seems not to be the way to go and it breaks deisctl later anyway so i'm not gonna write about that (or should i?).

my `sshKeyData` looks like that (the `(...)` in the middle is intended):

```
""sshKeyData"": {
    ""value"": ""(...)""
  },
```

Thanks in advance for any clues! I'm really excited to use deis and i hope that might be resolved :)
Mike",{},{}
