13032,IssuesEvent,2016-10-19 20:40:42+00:00,53344710,globus/globus-sdk-python,214142,jaswilli,6120321,globus,closed,"Token Introspect Doesn't Support ""include"" parameter","[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-sdk-python/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-sdk-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],3,"I ran into this while trying to use the introspect call.

[Per the docs](https://docs.globus.org/api/auth/reference/#token_introspection_post_v2_oauth2_token_introspect), you have the include the additional parameter: `{'include': 'identities_set'}` to get a full identity set as part of the introspect response.


For now I've got my code using `AuthClient.post` directly, so this is easy enough to work around, but we should add support for that parameter out of the box.
Since that's the only supported value, and that most introspect callers will want it, I would even argue that it should be set by default.",{},{}
13033,IssuesEvent,2017-07-24 19:51:16+00:00,53344710,globus/globus-sdk-python,1300022,sirosen,6120321,globus,opened,Make testsuite more robust to ConnectionErrors,"[{'id': 337675851, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-sdk-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}, {'id': 550334502, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-sdk-python/labels/error%20handling', 'name': 'error handling', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],0,"When we run the testsuite on Travis and AppVeyor, the build matrix is a decent size, and the total number of tests run starts to reach into the 1K order of magnitude.
Very often, with this many tests running, we'll see at least one ConnectionError, but it's just a bit of network flap.

To make the testsuite more robust, we just need to do some retries, and a potentially easy way is to clean and restart tests that hit connection errors. In any case, we need to handle these conditions a bit better than we currently do.",{},{}
13037,IssuesEvent,2016-10-31 20:06:12+00:00,53344710,globus/globus-sdk-python,1300022,sirosen,6120321,globus,opened,Add `ActivationRequirementsResponse.always_activated`,"[{'id': 337675851, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/globus/globus-sdk-python/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],0,"This should just be a property which returns the results of `self[""expires_in""] == -1`.

Otherwise, we'll get more confusion like the discussion in globus/globus-cli#119",{},{}
