13083,IssuesEvent,2017-07-20 22:12:37+00:00,71996613,blue-yonder/tsfresh,6116188,nils-braun,6234170,blue-yonder,closed,Make internal format more memory efficient.,"[{'id': 469228431, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/blue-yonder/tsfresh/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],1,"Currently our internal format is 

``` Python
{kind: pandas DataFrame with exactly two columns (the value and the id)}

```

So one example is 


```Python

{'a':      id  val
 57  500   74
 47  500   64
 8    10   56
 0    10   11
 46  500   70
 4    10   30
 45  500   65
 13   10   43
 51  500   77, 

'b':      id  val
 36   10   78
 67  500   60
 27   10   37
 69  500   12
 25   10   23
 34   10   44
 76  500   20
 68  500   79
 60  500    4
 23   10    7
 66  500   54}

```

The problem is the id column, this information is duplicated. Maybe we can have more nested dictionaries? Like

```
{kind: { id: values} }
```

Here, we could have the values as a plain numpy array

",{},{}
