```

The error can be easily fixed by changing the predict call and enclose the passed array in brackets.
```
# Original call which throws the error
#        y_pred[i] = ada.predict(X.iloc[i, :])[0]
# adding brackets solves it
y_pred[i] = ada.predict([X.iloc[i, :]])[0]
```

I am a total tsfresh novice and a python beginner. I am not sure why this error happens and if it may be caused by some new versions of the sklearn library or because i am using python 2.7? Maybe you are already aware and it is an intended exception?

Same error comes up in the basic forecasting notebook too.

Regards,",{},{}
