13198,IssuesEvent,2015-08-07 16:17:03+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1363114,nippoo,6392739,conda,opened,conda install python=3 now defaults to py33 packages not py34,[],[],0,"We used to run `conda install conda python=3 pip numpy matplotlib scipy h5py pyqt ipython-notebook requests vispy six -y` in our automated install script.

On the default miniconda3 install this would install the py3.4 packages.

Now this seems to install a bunch of py3.3-build packages, while still having a python 3.4 install, which breaks everything.

Fix is to manually specify `python=3.4` but this isn't ideal (it's in an automated install script and it should install the correct packages if the user has python 3.3 already installed in their root environment)",{},{}
13200,IssuesEvent,2016-03-08 15:11:04+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,2797735,mcg1969,6392739,conda,reopened,New solver should prefer newer versions,[],[],8,"@mcg1969 I just tried this (Using conda 4.0.1 on OSX):
