13211,IssuesEvent,2017-03-20 22:14:03+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,209902,gabrielcnr,6392739,conda,opened,conda clean --lock is not doing anything currently,[],[],0,"As of today (20 March 2017) the current implementation of `conda clean --lock` in HEAD(9d43c7e)   does not do anything at all.

I found out because I had to interrupt the `conda build` process when it was at the stage of reindexing the local channels and I noticed that the lock file got stuck inside the `noarch` local channel inside `conda-bld`.

The promise of the command is to ***remove all conda lock files***. I'm not sure which other lock files are set by conda, but I could definitely start by submitting a Pull Request that removes any lock files inside the local channels in `conda-bld` directory.
",{},{}
