13287,IssuesEvent,2017-06-30 21:32:29+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,16504363,dustinmichels,6392739,conda,closed,Trouble with virtual environments,[],[],1,"I deleted my miniconda3 folder, then reinstalled miniconda, then created a virtual env using `conda create -n <my_name> python.` I tried doing a developer installation of [bqplot](https://github.com/bloomberg/bqplot) using:
```
$ git clone https://github.com/bloomberg/bqplot.git
$ cd bqplot
$ pip install -e .
```
This appears to have installed some decencies inside my virtual environment, and some dependencies at root.

When I try to use bqplot, I get the error `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'traittypes'`. 

Inside my virtual env, I type `pip freeze` and `conda list` and indeed do not see `traittypes` listed. Outside the env, I type `pip freeze` and I see it listed.

Am I doing something wrong? Or is this a particular issue to bqplot? Or is the conda virtual environment behaving strangely?",{},{}
13288,IssuesEvent,2016-09-15 15:56:15+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,138657,scholer,6392739,conda,opened,Conda doesn't work after failed update.,[],[],0,"I did a routine ```conda update --all``` just now, but the update failed with a CondaOSError:

