After this, whenever I run any ```conda``` command or ```source```, it fails with this error:

    -bash: /Users/rasmus/anaconda3/bin/conda: /Users/rasmus/anaconda3/bin/python: bad interpreter: No such file or directory

When I run ```which python```, I get only the system python—as though Anaconda isn't even installed.

