13614,IssuesEvent,2016-08-10 18:45:31+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,6014209,yugangw-msft,6844498,Azure,closed,Omnibus of compute review asks,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/Compute', 'name': 'Compute', 'color': 'd4c5f9'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Azure/azure-cli/labels/P2', 'name': 'P2', 'color': 'd93f0b'}]","[{'login': 'yugangw-msft', 'id': 6014209, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6014209?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/yugangw-msft', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/yugangw-msft/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"_Please feel free to break out any part of this issue as required._

* ~~For cases where we have [id,name,rg] such as `az vm boot-diagnostics enable`, we should have a pattern for making this obvious~~. This is a general issue: Open #656
* Rename `usage list` to `list-usages` to match xplat and prevent a single-item group
* We should break out `--expand instanceView` from `az vm show` **or** provide an enum in help (and tab completion).
  * Another option is to create a `beta-show-instanceview` to make it clear this command only exists until the API supports a better pattern, as breaking out all expands across all RPs is a bit much. 
* Allow for masked interactive prompting for `--admin-password` during `vm create`
  * Show if a password is required but not supplied
  * Show if an empty `--admin-password` is supplied, such as `az vm create --admin-password --image ubuntults`
* Access extension - we should call out the rights of users in the help text

",{},{}
13617,IssuesEvent,2016-07-29 19:17:41+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,10136041,BurtBiel,6844498,Azure,opened,[Generic Update] we should show fields for objects that aren't set,[],[],0,"Today, we only show available fields on the object being mutated as options for the parameter path.  However, in the case of a VM without data disks, we give no hints as to which properties can be set--the user has to find a VM with a data disk and learn from that pattern.  We should find the SDK object that corresponds to the object (data disk in this case) and show available properties from that object.  This allows users to fill out empty fields without having to find a filled out example first.",{},{}
