13799,IssuesEvent,2016-01-28 23:57:25+00:00,25611422,openaddresses/machine,58730,migurski,6895392,openaddresses,closed,Don't apply abbreviation expansions for sources in non en-US locale,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/openaddresses/machine/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],3,"In Italy, most roads are named `Via xyz` where [*via*](https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/via#Italian) means *road* or *street* in English. The current [abbreviation expansion code](https://github.com/openaddresses/machine/blob/master/openaddr/expand.py#L214) transforms each of these to *Viaduct*. See [Firenze](https://github.com/openaddresses/openaddresses/blob/master/sources/it/52/firenze.json) [for example](http://s3.amazonaws.com/data.openaddresses.io/runs/57159/it/52/firenze.zip).

As the expansion code is only intended for [US English](https://github.com/openaddresses/machine/blob/master/openaddr/expand.py#L2) abbreviations, it doesn't make sense to apply it to sources outside the US.",{},{}
