14598,IssuesEvent,2015-03-31 21:45:44+00:00,27888295,SatelliteQE/nailgun,53362,omaciel,8754276,SatelliteQE,opened,The ``get_client_kwargs`` method should should copy ``self`` attributes before removing the ``url`` attribute,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/SatelliteQE/nailgun/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"The ``get_client_kwargs`` method is removing the ``url`` attribute from the class instance itself. Instead it should probably copy all attributes to the local scope, remove the attribute, and return this copy.

```python
In [1]: from nailgun.config import ServerConfig

In [2]: ibm02 = ServerConfig(url='https://www.example.com', auth=('admin', 'changeme'), verify=False)

In [3]: vars(ibm02)
Out[3]:
{'auth': ('admin', 'changeme'),
 'url': 'https://www.example.com',
 'verify': False}

In [4]: ibm02.get_client_kwargs()
Out[4]: {'auth': ('admin', 'changeme'), 'verify': False}

In [5]: vars(ibm02)
Out[5]: {'auth': ('admin', 'changeme'), 'verify': False}

In [6]: ibm02.auth
Out[6]: ('admin', 'changeme')

In [7]: ibm02.url
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
AttributeError                            Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-7-0228738b37af> in <module>()
----> 1 ibm02.url

AttributeError: 'ServerConfig' object has no attribute 'url'

```",{},{}
14616,IssuesEvent,2018-07-31 11:11:02+00:00,24245737,projectmesa/mesa,13568919,Corvince,8754505,projectmesa,closed,Multiprocessing doesn't seem to work,[],[],3,"**Describe the bug**
I have REST calls in my agent's `step()` function which are blocking in nature. And it seems that when a particular agent issues the REST call, the execution of other agents is also stalled.

**Expected behavior**
Since mesa has multiprocessing support, other agents should also continue to execute their respective `step()` functions.

**To Reproduce**
Just add a blocking call in the agent's step function and see if that prevents other agent's from executing their logic.

**Additional Context**
I am using `RandomActivation()` because I want all the agents to be woken up once per epoch.
",{},{}
14639,IssuesEvent,2017-03-22 11:01:46+00:00,24043280,sshuttle/sshuttle,229415,kwill,8774006,sshuttle,opened,Document how to use /etc/sshuttle files,[],[],0,"I've installed `sshuttle` 0.78.1-1 on Ubuntu 16.10. From the terminal I can successfully run:

    sshuttle --auto-hosts --daemon --remote=remote_user@host:port ip

I'd like to make this connection:

* always start when my computer starts (i.e. run as a daemon/service)
* uses the local user ssh key for the ssh connection (`/home/local_user/.ssh/key_rsa`)

this is so that:

* I don't have to remember to connect every time I start my machine
* I don't have to enter my sudo or ssh password every time

As far as I can tell I should be doing this with `/etc/sshuttle/tunnel.conf` and `/etc/sshuttle/prefixes.conf` but it's not clear to me:
* how to map sshtunnel command-line values to ssh_config values
* how I would define more than one sshtunnel connection in these files
* what kind of files I would put in `/etc/sshuttle/pre-start.d/` and `/etc/sshuttle/post-stop.d/`

Some documentation or an example would be helpful.

(As an alternative, I've also tried defining a .desktop file that invokes sshuttle using gksudo or pkexec, but this effectively runs sshuttle as root which skips the ssh key file.)",{},{}
