15042,IssuesEvent,2018-04-08 00:52:49+00:00,26876372,dateutil/dateutil,1377457,pganssle,9849410,dateutil,closed,relativedelta division,"[{'id': 180110525, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/relativedelta', 'name': 'relativedelta', 'color': 'fbca04', 'default': False}, {'id': 149492531, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/dateutil/dateutil/labels/wontfix', 'name': 'wontfix', 'color': 'ffffff', 'default': True}]",[],2,"In `datetime`, it is possible to divide two `timedelta`s:

```python
import datetime
print(datetime.timedelta(1) / datetime.timedelta(2))  # output: 05
```

However the same is not possible in `dateutil` with `relativedelta`:

```python
import dateutil.relativedelta
dateutil.relativedelta.relativedelta(days=1) / dateutil.relativedelta.relativedelta(days=2)
# TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for /: 'relativedelta' and 'relativedelta'
```

I feel it would be good to include this functionality in `dateutil`. I know it would not make sense in some cases but I feel in many it would. Thoughts?",{},{}
