15232,IssuesEvent,2018-02-24 17:44:57+00:00,4637221,powerline/powerline,3293723,renyuneyun,10100576,powerline,opened,Unexpected spaces after the end of right widgets,[],[],0,"I'm encountering unexpected spaces after the right widgets. Actually this has happened for a long time, but only until now did I consider it a problem.

Here are two screenshots illustrating the problem (the problem is there with any actions needed from me):

<img width=""642"" alt=""powerline_weather_right_mismatch"" src=""https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3293723/36633157-44d6cb92-1988-11e8-9454-387f54b6ec4c.png"">

In this setting, I'm using the default one-line setting (theme) with the weather widget configured. There is one extra space to the right of the weather widget.

<img width=""641"" alt=""powerline_weather_right_mismatch_2"" src=""https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3293723/36633161-660efc26-1988-11e8-86c3-33cf41c15123.png"">

In this setting, I'm using something similar to [this two-line setting](https://github.com/yongjhih/rc/blob/master/.config/powerline/themes/shell/default.json). There is **one** extra space to the right of the weather widget, and **two** extra spaces for the second line.
