This doesn't seem to be related to the weather widget, because I have tried to remove it and the result is the same.

I'm using zsh, on archlinux x86_64 (presumably not related). The powerline instance is the one (py3 version) provided in the official repo (v2.6).",{},{}
15240,IssuesEvent,2016-05-30 20:41:37+00:00,4637221,powerline/powerline,4508103,svenpilz,10100576,powerline,opened,Wrong sysfs filenames in battery segment?,[],[],0,"Hello everybody!

I was looking at why the battery segment (segments/common/bat.py) wasn't working on my machine. Turned out it was looking for batteries in sysfs and specifically the files `energy_(full|now)`, which don't exist on my machine (Linux 4.5). Seems they are prefixed with `charged` instead `energy`. Changing it resulted in usual energy readings :).


Sven",{},{}
