15483,IssuesEvent,2017-11-23 06:36:05+00:00,66823715,intel-analytics/BigDL,20787576,zhangxiaoli73,10941215,intel-analytics,opened,Graph schedule takes too much time for small model or small batchsize,[],[],0,"When testing deepspeech model inference, found:
for deepspeech model with batchsize=1, graph process (not including nodes forward time) time takes about 10% of whole model time cost.
use another lenet model with batchsize=1, graph process (not including nodes forward time) time takes about 35% of whole model time cost. Increasing batchsize=32, it takes about 8%.

As in graph forward, schedule operations are fixed for a model. So when batchsize is small, nodes forward time will be less, but graph process time will not be reduced.
",{},{}
