15580,IssuesEvent,2018-05-11 04:37:07+00:00,30895522,pvlib/pvlib-python,4383303,wholmgren,11037261,pvlib,closed,tracking algorithm: projection of the sun vector in the panel oriented coordinate system,[],[],1,"Hi,
I suspect that for the projection on the y'-axis in the panel oriented coordinate system (x', y', z'), it's not ""-z * sind(axis_tilt)"" but ""+z *  sind(axis_tilt)"".

According to the definition of the panel oriented system, if the rotation axis is 90 degrees tilted the y' axis should be coincident with the vertical z axis pointing in the same direction.

Can anyone confirm or explain why it's a minus?

Thanks",{},{}
