16362,IssuesEvent,2017-03-07 21:04:08+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,4319174,egede,13271048,ganga-devs,opened,Provide instructions for running tests,[],[],0,"@VanyaBelyaev has asked for instructions on how to get the testing framework up and running. To set it up from scratch seems actually to be far from trivial. On lxplus7, I went through the steps below. If somebody can make it shorter I would be pleased.

```
# Upgrade virtualenv as the default version provides too old a
# version of setuptools
pip install --upgrade --user virtualenv

# Subsequent virtualenv command fails without this.
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/releases/LCG_87/Python/2.7.10/x86_64-centos7-gcc62-opt/lib

# Create a virtualenv for the testing
python ./.local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/virtualenv.py testGanga

# Go into the virtualenv for the testing
cd testGanga
bash --norc
source bin/activate

# Clone the Ganga repository
git clone https://github.com/ganga-devs/ganga.git

# Install Ganga dependencies, including those for the testing.
cd ganga
pip install --upgrade -r requirements.txt

# Get ready for the testing.
cd python
export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:`pwd`

# Run a test
py.test Ganga/test/Unit/Notebook
```

and then for subsequent logins (where the installation is already there)

```
# Subsequent virtualenv command fails without this.
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/releases/LCG_87/Python/2.7.10/x86_64-centos7-gcc62-opt/lib

# Go into the virtualenv for the testing
cd testGanga
bash --norc
source bin/activate

# Get ready for the testing.
cd ganga/python
export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:`pwd`

# Run a test
py.test Ganga/test/Unit/Notebook
```",{},{}
