16623,IssuesEvent,2017-01-20 01:56:33+00:00,43852872,PulpQE/pulp-smash,16638409,goosemania,14839747,PulpQE,opened,Test the sync /upload of RPM with large metadata,[],[],0,"With Pulp 2.12.1+ , metadata for RPM/SRPM units will be stored in the compressed form in DB. This change allows Pulp to have packages with larger metadata than it was possible before.

For testing purposes one will need:
- either to create **an RPM which filelists metadata exceeds ~9MB but is less than ~15MB**
- or to use any existing RPM with large filelists metadata, 
e.g. https://fedorapeople.org/groups/katello/releases/yum/foreman/1.13/el6/x86_64/nodejs-babel-preset-es2015-6.6.0-2.el6.noarch.rpm

Verify that sync or upload of such RPM does not result in  `DocumentTooLarge` error.

As for the upgrade, the migration will be run and the metadata for all the existing units will be compressed. I do not think there is something specific to test here, just make sure all the rpm sync/upload/publish-related tests are still working after upgrade.

Redmine issue: https://pulp.plan.io/issues/723",{},{}
