17753,IssuesEvent,2016-11-14 14:25:30+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,3705643,konradkonrad,19666847,raiden-network,opened,Fix antipatterns in pytests,[],[],0,"In some places (at least 
https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/master/raiden/tests/unit/test_service.py#L40-L55) we are manually setting class attributes in order to reset them at the bottom of the test functions. This can lead to hard to explain behavior if single tests (x)fail, because the reset calls will not be executed.
This should be fixed by using pytests [`monkeypatch`](http://doc.pytest.org/en/latest/monkeypatch.html) instead.",{},{}
