17832,IssuesEvent,2017-06-26 22:29:25+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,Passing global statements (e.g. function definitions) to tasks,[],[],0,"Currently task needs to be self-contained, in that all function definition and module import needs to be done inside task. It is therefore not possible to do

```
def func():
   something

[step]
task:
   func()
```

which is quite inconvenient. Perhaps we should allow tasks to execute definitions in global sections.",{},{}
17833,IssuesEvent,2017-06-14 04:45:06+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,opened,explicit path map / rename with options to_host and from_host,"[{'id': 325435539, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/request', 'name': 'request', 'color': '159818', 'default': False}]",[],0,"I have a need to copy data from remote host to local host under another name. This is currently done with `from_host` and then a bunch of rename operations. We might be able to help under this situation by allowing some thing like

```
to_host={'local_file': 'remote_file'},
from_host={'remote_file': 'local_file'}
```
in addition to 

```
to_host='local_file', from_host='loca_file'
```
The underlying explanation is that SoS would not translate map with an explicit path map.",{},{}
17841,IssuesEvent,2017-04-29 20:22:34+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Interface for removing obsolete task files.,[],"[{'login': 'gaow', 'id': 917985, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/917985?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/gaow', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/gaow/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, {'login': 'BoPeng', 'id': 9889312, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars2.githubusercontent.com/u/9889312?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/BoPeng', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/BoPeng/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",8,"A single task could have `.task`, `.status`, `.res`, and engine specific files such as `.pbs`. Over time, sos tends to accumulate a large number of such files, which, in addition to file management issues, actually could slow down sos because `sos status` matches all jobs and query them all.

We of course do not want to remove running jobs, also jobs from the same batch because they are still actively monitors, and perhaps not ""unknown"" jobs because they might be submitted from another machine. I suppose this has to be a manual process using something along the line of

```
sos remove --completed
```
and
```
sos remove --failed
```
and perhaps
```
sos remove --tasks
```

Another possibility is to archive these files... zip them and allow sos to retrieve them later on. 

Any comment?",{},{}
17843,IssuesEvent,2017-03-07 15:48:58+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Rstudio notebook,"[{'id': 325435541, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/discussion', 'name': 'discussion', 'color': 'cc317c', 'default': False}]",[],1,"also has multi-language support etc. http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/authoring_knitr_engines.html 

So is SoS really good at anything?

1. jupyter, compete with RStudio, losing battle?
2. workflow, facing a huge crowd of workflow systems
3. Simple sos format that unites 1 and 2 would be the selling point?",{},{}
