18304,IssuesEvent,2018-07-21 12:43:25+00:00,68376693,pybel/pybel,5069736,cthoyt,22892058,pybel,closed,Mutation test pybel.constants,"[{'id': 540964567, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw1NDA5NjQ1Njc=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pybel/pybel/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}, {'id': 443704420, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw0NDM3MDQ0MjA=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pybel/pybel/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '128A0C', 'default': True}, {'id': 540965106, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw1NDA5NjUxMDY=', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pybel/pybel/labels/low%20priority', 'name': 'low priority', 'color': 'f9d0c4', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Nothing should break if the values of the constants in `pybel.constants` are changed, because they are always referred to through the pybel source and testing code by their variable name.

The idea is to systematically change the values of each variable - one at a time, add garbage text to the end of the constant, and rerun the testing suite - and see if anything breaks. Nothing should, so if it does, that probably points to code where a value is used rather than the reference.

This would be a good issue for someone who doesn't know much about the project but wants to make a contribution!",{},{}
