18642,IssuesEvent,2017-05-31 14:33:27+00:00,36093931,sentinelsat/sentinelsat,1778160,valgur,29057552,sentinelsat,opened,Replace positional arguments with keyword arguments,[],[],0,"I propose we replace the CLI positional arguments `<user> <password> <geojson>` with equivalent ""optional"" arguments (such as `-u,--user`, `-p,--password` and `-g,--geometry`). The `user` and `password` args would still be required arguments in one form or another, of course.

Here are some of the possible benefits of that change:
* The user does not need to remember the order of the positional args and can pass arguments in any order. A minor convenience.
* It would allow us to implement alternative ways of passing credentials to our CLI, e.g. through [environment variables](http://click.pocoo.org/5/options/#dynamic-defaults-for-prompts), INI or .netrc files (#90).
* Would enable alternative arguments for passing AOI geometries, if need be (#114).
* One of ours goals for release v1.0 should be stability and backwards-compatibility of the CLI and API. So now would be a good time for this backwards-incompatible change. This would provide greater flexibility for us in the future, though.

Do you agree?",{},{}
